Business Brief -- Maxum Health Corp.:
   Imaging Firm Sets Charge
   To Replace Older Machines
Maxum said new MRI systems cost between $1.6 million and
$2.2 million, and that the change will reduce the average age
of its systems by one year, to about 2.5 years.
   Maxum went public in September with an initial offering of
1.5 million shares at $12.50 each. The stock closed yesterday
at $11.375, up 12.5 cents, in American Stock Exchange
composite trading.
   Comparable results for the 1990 first quarter weren't
available.
   Separately, Maxum said it acquired a Dallas center that
provides diagnostic imaging services for physicians. Terms of
the transaction weren't disclosed.